frameDefinitions: This frame contains words describing physical experiences that can affect virtually any part of the body.
In this frame the Patient, an inorganic item, undergoes a chemical process which renders it less useful, desirable or stable. '' '
An Entity (generally food) is exposed to a Heat_source whose Temperature may also be specified.
In this frame, the temperature of an Item changes.
The words in this frame describe a period of time, as opposed to a point in time.
A Communicator conveys a Message to an Addressee; the Topic and Medium of the communication also may be expressed.
frameExamples: Bacon was <t>frying</t> in the pan, and a great heap of eggs already lay steaming on a plate.
The house had <t>cooled</t> <t>off</t> by a few more degrees by midnight, and we finally managed to eat a bite.
The best <t>time</t> of year for planting tends to be fairly regular.
Let's hope it did n't have time to <t>communicate</t> any of its findings to its overlords.
listRoleDefinitions: The Experiencer is the being who has a physical experience on some part of his  or her body, or internally. Often information about this frame element is incorporated as a possessive determiner into the constituent expressing the Body Part, in which case it is not tagged separately (from Body Part), as shown below: My legs <t>hurt</t>! Sometimes, however, this frame element is expressed as an External Argument in its own right:  <fex name='Experiencer'>I</fex> <t>hurt</t> all over! Here, the phrase <ment>all over</ment> can be considered a kind of generalized Body Part expression, and the pronoun <ment>I</ment> expresses the Experiencer independently. With nouns and adjectives in this frame, the separate expression of the Experiencer is more common: <fex name='Experiencer'>I</fex> have a <t>pain</t> in my leg.

This role is the location on the body where the physical experience takes place, typically expressed as External Argument, often as PP complement: <fex name='Body_part'>My legs</fex> are a little <t>sore</t>. I'm a little <t>sore</t> <fex name='Body_part'>in my legs</fex>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> undergoes a change.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Patient</fen> corrodes.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Patient</fen> corrodes.
The <fen>Entity</fen> (often a food item)  that absorbs heat.
The <fen>Container</fen> that holds the <fen>Entity</fen> that absorbs the heat.
This role identifies the object that directly supplies heat to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the heat absorption takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application occurs.
The entity whose temperature changes.
The scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.  This role is rarely expressed.
The time at which the change in temperature occurs.
The location at which the <fen>Item</fen> changes temperature.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>State</fen>'s duration.  In this frame, the duration can be inexact.
An ongoing state whose duration can be measured.
The sentient entity that uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a <fen>Message</fen> to the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
<fen>Message</fen> is a proposition or set of propositions that the <fen>Communicator</fen> wants the <fen>Addressee</fen> to believe or take for granted.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the <fen>Message</fen> pertains. It is normally expressed as a PP Complement headed by 'about', but in some cases it can appear as a direct object.
The physical or abstract setting in which the <fen>Message</fen> is conveyed.
The time at which the communication takes place.
The location where the act of communication occurs.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The bikes</fex> rusted from their former beauty.
<fex>Bacon</fex> frying in the pan and scenting the air
Five fat sausages were frying <fex>in the pan</fex>
Food was placed to sizzle <fex>on the barbecue </fex>.
<fex>Five minutes ago</fex>the eggs weren't boiling yet.
<fex>In the kitchen</fex> the meat sizzled in the oven and a big pan of potatoes stood on the hob
The raw fish that is to be eaten as sushi has to be meticulously prepared and must first be chilled <fex>in temperature</fex> to exactly above freezing point.
<fex>He was a great actor</fex> in his time.
<fex>He</fex> finds it hard to communicate with people, not least his separated parents .
How do you communicate to them <fex>that you really like them</fex> ?
Had someone communicated to the capital <fex>about the flagrant disregard of the religious law</fex> ?
Opinions are usually communicated <fex>over the telephone</fex> and are often given within 24 hours.
